This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it discusses a system for real-time distributed stream processing. It may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category as it deals with resource utilization and scheduling. The Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses optimizing resource utilization while minimizing network latency. The Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category is relevant as the paper discusses minimizing network distance between components. Finally, the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category may be relevant as the paper discusses implementing resource-aware scheduling within the Storm system.
